article.headline: Lehigh 88, Harvard 79
article.story: BETHLEHEM, Pa. (AP) -- Jose Olivero scored a career-high 24 points to lead Lehigh past Harvard 88-79 on Saturday night. Ra Tiah added 16 points and Austen Rowland scored 14 for Lehigh (3-3), which was 8-of-16 from beyond the arc. After Lehigh jumped out to a 55-43 lead to start the second half, Harvard (0-5) scored nine straight points to close within a single point at 62-61. But a pair of free throws and a layup by Rowland put Lehigh back up by five, and Harvard got no closer. Matt Stehle led Harvard with 17 points, while David Giovacchini scored 14 and Kevin Rogus added 10.
